Refund Rate
MEDIUM
For each seller, calculate the refund rate: number of refunded orders divided by total orders. Round to 2 decimal places. Only show sellers with more than 1 order.

▼
TABLE SCHEMA — click to view
orders( seller_id INT, order_id INT, status TEXT )
Sample Input
seller_id	order_id	status
1	101	Completed
1	102	Refunded
1	103	Completed
2	104	Refunded
2	105	Refunded
3	106	Completed
Expected Output
seller_id	refund_rate
1	0.33
2	1

select seller_id, round(sum(case when status='Refunded' then 1.0 else 0 end)/count(*),2) as refund_rate
from orders
group by seller_id
having count(order_id)>1
